        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(memory): carry source actor context into recall",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Carries `SourceActor` from inbound context through embedded runs and plugin tool context.\n- Exposes the same source actor context to memory corpus supplements for `memory_search` and `memory_get`.\n- Adds memory prompt/flush guidance to preserve participant attribution instead of merging another participant's facts into the operator/user profile.\n\n## Stack\n\nThis is stacked after #96738, `codex/signal-mention-facts-context`, and `codex/source-actor-context-contract`. Until those land, this PR's diff will include its dependencies.\n\n## Production impact\n\nNo storage migration and no backend-specific behavior. This is not Honcho-specific: it adds a generic runtime/tool/memory contract that memory backends and supplements can consume. Core memory search still filters by existing session/source visibility; this PR does not claim a new per-person storage partition.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/openclaw-tools.plugin-context.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/inbound-meta.test.ts extensions/memory-core/index.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.citations.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/channels/inbound-event/context.test.ts extensions/signal/src/monitor/event-handler.mention-gating.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/openclaw-tools.plugin-context.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/inbound-meta.test.ts extensions/memory-core/index.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.citations.test.ts src/channels/inbound-event/context.test.ts extensions/signal/src/monitor/event-handler.mention-gating.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`\n",
